# Notes on setting up python environment for python-tools

We use python2.7 for this project, since this is the version of python opencv available as part of the ros modules

## Install python2 virtualenv
 - you will need your jumpcloud username and password for this
 - `sudo pip install virtualenv`

## Create a new virtual environment
python -m virtualenv python2-workspace

Here, python2-workspace is the name given to the virtual environment. You can given any name of your choice

## Activating the virtual environment for this project
source python2-workspace/bin/activate

You can de-activate using the command `deactivate`

## Install required python packages
To install the required python packages, activate the virtual environment and then

pip install -r requirements.txt
